# getting all countries
countries = np.asarray(df_confirmed["country"])
countries1 = np.asarray(df_covid19["country"])
# Continent_code to Continent_names
continents = {
    'NA': 'North America',
    'SA': 'South America', 
    'AS': 'Asia',
    'OC': 'Australia',
    'AF': 'Africa',
    'EU' : 'Europe',
    'na' : 'Others'
}

# Defininng Function for getting continent code for country.
def country_to_continent_code(country):
    try:
        return pc.country_alpha2_to_continent_code(pc.country_name_to_country_alpha2(country))
    except :
        return 'na'

#Collecting Continent Information
df_confirmed.insert(2,"continent", [continents[country_to_continent_code(country)] for country in countries[:]])
df_deaths.insert(2,"continent",  [continents[country_to_continent_code(country)] for country in countries[:]])
df_covid19.insert(1,"continent",  [continents[country_to_continent_code(country)] for country in countries1[:]])
df_table.insert(1,"continent",  [continents[country_to_continent_code(country)] for country in df_table["Country_Region"].values])

# Obtain Population growth (average of 3 years) to estimate Population in 2019

wb_data_growth = wbdata.get_dataframe({'SP.POP.GROW':'Population, growth_annual'}, data_date=(datetime.datetime(2016, 1, 1), datetime.datetime(2018, 1, 1)),convert_date=False).reset_index()
wb_data_growth = pd.DataFrame(wb_data_growth.groupby(['country'])['Population, growth_annual'].mean().reset_index())
wb_data_growth['percent_growth_annual'] = (1 + wb_data_growth['Population, growth_annual'] / 100)
#wb_data_growth.head()

# Merge population metrics with updated covid-19 data to compute variable metrics
wb_data_merge4 = df_covid19.merge(wb_data_merge3[['country','pop_19_total','pop_19_density_sqkm']],how='right',left_on=['country'],right_on=['country'])
wb_data_merge4['Confirmed_norm'] = (wb_data_merge4['Confirmed'] / wb_data_merge4['pop_19_total']) # COnfirmed cases divided by total population
wb_data_merge4['Death_norm'] = (wb_data_merge4['Deaths'] / wb_data_merge4['pop_19_total']) # Death cases devided by total population
wb_data_merge4['Confirmed_norm_M'] = (wb_data_merge4['Confirmed_norm'] * 1000000) # Normalised confirmed * 1 million
wb_data_merge4['Death_norm_M'] = (wb_data_merge4['Death_norm'] * 1000000) # Normalised deaths * 1 million
